# Multi-User WhatsApp Pro — Integration Guide

## What was added

Three new source files live in `src/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/UserSessionManager.ts` | Per-user session store (proData, sock, qrCode, WS clients) |
| `src/MultiUserEngine.ts` | Baileys socket lifecycle — one engine per user |
| `src/multiUserRouter.ts` | Express router for all user-scoped `/api/u/:userId/*` endpoints |
| `src/multiUserWS.ts` | WebSocket patch so each client is identified by userId |

---

## Minimal changes required in `server.ts`

Add these lines to `server.ts` (after the existing imports):

```ts
// ─── MULTI-USER ADDITIONS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
import { initSessionManager } from './src/UserSessionManager.js';
import { initUserEngine } from './src/MultiUserEngine.js';
import { multiUserRouter } from './src/multiUserRouter.js';
import { patchWSSForMultiUser } from './src/multiUserWS.js';
```

Inside `startServer()`, **before** any route registrations, add:

```ts
// Init the multi-user session manager
const sessionMgr = initSessionManager(BASE_DATA_DIR);

// Patch WebSocket server for per-user routing
patchWSSForMultiUser(wss);

// Mount the multi-user API router
// All per-user endpoints are under /api/u/:userId/...
app.use('/api/u/:userId', multiUserRouter);

// Auto-start the "default" session to keep backwards compatibility
const defaultSession = sessionMgr.getOrCreate('default');
initUserEngine(defaultSession);
```

