## Frontend changes

### 1. WebSocket identification

After opening the WebSocket, send an IDENTIFY message:

```js
const ws = new WebSocket(`ws://localhost:3000?userId=${userId}`);
// OR after open:
ws.onopen = () => {
  ws.send(JSON.stringify({ type: 'IDENTIFY', userId: currentUserId }));
};

ws.onmessage = (e) => {
  const msg = JSON.parse(e.data);
  if (msg.userId && msg.userId !== currentUserId) return; // ignore other users' events
  // handle msg.type: 'QR_CODE', 'CONNECTION_STATE', 'NEW_MESSAGE', etc.
};
```

### 2. API requests

Change all API calls to include the userId:

**Before:**
```js
fetch('/api/connection-status')
fetch('/api/send-message', { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify({ jid, text }) })
```

**After:**
```js
const uid = getCurrentUserId(); // e.g. stored in localStorage after login
fetch(`/api/u/${uid}/connection-status`)
fetch(`/api/u/${uid}/send-message`, { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify({ jid, text }) })
```

### 3. User login flow

To create/start a session, call:
```js
// Start session and get QR
const res = await fetch(`/api/u/${userId}/refresh-qr`);

// Poll connection status
const status = await fetch(`/api/u/${userId}/connection-status`).then(r => r.json());
// status.qrCode contains the QR (base64 or raw string)
// status.state: 'close' | 'connecting' | 'open'
```

